          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-215 Bind ost/mdt to specific nids",
        "message": "LU-215 Bind ost/mdt to specific nids\n\nThe goal of the patch attached to this bug is to make NUMIOA factor\nmanagement easier, by giving the ability to restrict the NIDs that a\ntarget (mdt or ost) registers on the MGS. By this means we can enforce\nclient requests to go through the most appropriate network interface,\nie the one that minimizes the NUMIOA factor.\n\nBinding is controlled via the new '--network' option of mkfs.lustre and\ntunefs.lustre commands.\nThis option takes as values one or more LNET networks. At mount.lustre\ntime the target registers on the MGS with only the NIDs that pertain to the\nnetworks specified. If no specific network is given, all NIDs are registered.\n\nChange-Id: I8f5e8ac71dd0d81948af11edc58572001207c37d\nBugzilla: 22078\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
  },
